% -------------------------- create/choose folder

- in terminal: go to folder
> cd Desktop\Nancy\PhD

- initialise Git repo
> git init

- tell Git where the remote repo is (i.e., on the internet) (if remote repo doesn't exist, you need to create it) by copying and pasting:
> git remote add origin git@github.com:nancypayne/PhD.git


%-------------------------- if you want to change stuff... change it (e.g., update file)

- to update to origin,
> git add --all

> git commit -m "message here"

First time:
> git push --set-upstream origin master

Every other time:
> git push origin 


% ------------------------ to link up the contents of a folder in a new location

- in terminal, go to folder
> git init

> git remote add origin git@github.com:nancypayne/repo_name.git

> git pull origin master


% ------------------------ to link up work computer (using Github Desktop)

- below list of changes, add "summary" message and click "Commit to master"

- Click "Push origin" to push changes to Github website